05/11/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK announced on Tuesday (4 November) that it was establishing an authority to fight corruption in the province.
The new Investigation Task Force would become operational by mid-November.
Its investigations into Kosovo's public sector would focus on both local and international officials.
Results would be passed on to law enforcement authorities for criminal action.
In other news Tuesday, Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic released a White Book that spells out Belgrade's war crimes accusations against Kosovo Liberation Army members.
He told reporters that the publication should help NATO and The Hague tribunal prosecute ethnic Albanian war crimes suspects.
It provides the names of 156 members of ethnic Albanian groups.
(AFP - 04/11/03)
